Governor Seyi Makinde of Oyo State has confirmed the second COVID-19-related death in the state. Makinde gave the confirmation via a post on his Twitter handle early Monday. He said, sadly, “one of the new COVID-19 cases announced yesterday, passed away this morning. This brings the number of COVID-19 related deaths in the state to two.“ “So, there are currently eight active cases in Oyo State” he added. OYO STATE COVID-19 TASK FORCE UPDATE (APRIL 26, 2020) Sadly, one of the new COVID-19 cases announced yesterday, passed away this morning. This brings the number of COVID-19 related deaths in the state to two. So, there are currently eight active cases in Oyo State. pic.twitter.com/Fqj8s3ExBx — Seyi Makinde (@seyiamakinde) April 26, 2020  On Sunday night, Nigeria recorded 91 new cases of COVID-19, with the total confirmed cases currently at 1273.